SB 711/25 – JPR CF 6lr3416
By: Senator McKay
Introduced and read first time: February 2, 2026
Assigned to: Judicial Proceedings
Committee Report: Favorable
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: February 16, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Off–Highway Recreational Vehicle Recreation Oversight Board – Establishment
3 FOR the purpose of establishing the Off–Highway Recreational Vehicle Recreation
4 Oversight Board to advise the Secretary of Natural Resources on certain matters;
5 and generally relating to the Off–Highway Recreational Vehicle Recreation
6 Oversight Board.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Natural Resources
9 Section 5–1011.1
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Natural Resources
15 5–1011.1.
16 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
17 INDICATED.
18 (2) “BOARD” MEANS THE OFF–HIGHWAY RECREATIONAL VEHICLE
19 RECREATION OVERSIGHT BOARD.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0480*

2 SENATE BILL 480
1 (3) “FUND” MEANS THE OFF–HIGHWAY RECREATIONAL VEHICLE
2 TRAIL FUND ESTABLISHED UNDER § 5–1011 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
3 (B) THERE IS AN OFF–HIGHWAY RECREATIONAL VEHICLE RECREATION
4 OVERSIGHT BOARD.
5 (C) (1) THE BOARD CONSISTS OF THE FOLLOWING MEMBERS,
6 APPOINTED BY THE GOVERNOR:
7 (I) ONE REPRESENTATIVE OF THE MARYLAND OFF–HIGHWAY
8 VEHICLE ALLIANCE;
9 (II) ONE REPRESENTATIVE OF THE MARYLAND MOTORCYCLE
10 DEALERS ASSOCIATION;
11 (III) ONE REPRESENTATIVE OF THE AMERICAN MOTORCYCLIST
12 ASSOCIATION DISTRICT 7;
13 (IV) ONE INDIVIDUAL REPRESENTING ALL–TERRAIN VEHICLE,
14 UTILITY TERRAIN VEHICLE, OR SIDE–BY–SIDE VEHICLE DRIVERS; AND
15 (V) ONE INDIVIDUAL REPRESENTING ON– AND OFF–ROAD
16 MOTOR VEHICLE DRIVERS.
17 (2) EACH MEMBER SHALL BE A RESIDENT OF THE STATE.
18 (D) FROM AMONG ITS MEMBERS, THE BOARD SHALL ELECT A CHAIR EACH
19 YEAR.
20 (E) (1) THE TERM OF A MEMBER IS 4 YEARS.
21 (2) THE TERMS OF MEMBERS ARE STAGGERED AS REQUIRED BY THE
22 TERMS PROVIDED FOR MEMBERS OF THE BOARD ON OCTOBER 1, 2026.
23 (3) AT THE END OF A TERM, A MEMBER CONTINUES TO SERVE UNTIL
24 A SUCCESSOR IS APPOINTED AND QUALIFIES.
25 (4) A MEMBER WHO IS APPOINTED AFTER A TERM HAS BEGUN SERVES
26 ONLY FOR THE REST OF THE TERM AND UNTIL A SUCCESSOR IS APPOINTED AND
27 QUALIFIES.

SENATE BILL 480 3
1 (5) IF A VACANCY OCCURS AMONG THE MEMBERS, THE GOVERNOR
2 SHALL PROMPTLY APPOINT A SUCCESSOR WHO SHALL SERVE UNTIL THE TERM
3 EXPIRES.
4 (F) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL PROVIDE STAFF FOR THE BOARD.
5 (2) ADDITIONAL SUPPORT FOR THE BOARD SHALL BE PROVIDED BY:
6 (I) THE SECRETARY, OR THE SECRETARY’S DESIGNEE;
7 (II) THE MARYLAND PARK SERVICE;
8 (III) THE FOREST SERVICE;
9 (IV) THE WILDLIFE AND HERITAGE SERVICE; AND
10 (V) ONE REPRESENTATIVE OF EACH COUNTY IN WHICH AN
11 OFF–HIGHWAY RECREATIONAL VEHICLE TRAIL MAINTAINED BY THE DEPARTMENT
12 IS LOCATED, DESIGNATED BY THE DEPARTMENT.
13 (G) THE BOARD SHALL MEET AT LEAST QUARTERLY.
14 (H) THE BOARD SHALL ADVISE THE SECRETARY ON THE OPERATION,
15 ACQUISITION, REGULATION, AND GENERAL OVERSIGHT OF OFF–HIGHWAY
16 RECREATIONAL VEHICLE TRAILS AND RECREATION IN THE STATE.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the terms of the initial
18 appointed members of the Off–Highway Recreational Vehicle Recreation Oversight Board
19 established under Section 1 of this Act shall expire as follows:
20 (1) one member in 2027;
21 (2) two members in 2028; and
22 (3) two members in 2029.
23 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
24 October 1, 2026.

